The paper deals with channel state information (CSI) feedback in massive multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The proposed method uses deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs), to compress the CSI matrix, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the trade-off between compression rate and reconstruction quality, which is a topic related to optimization and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the practical implementation of the proposed method in a frequency division duplex (FDD) system, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper focuses on the application of the proposed method in massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to wireless communications (cs.MM).
